    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="letter">
                <div type="text">
                    <opener>
                        <placeName>Hitcham, Hadleigh, Suffolk</placeName>
                        <date>13 July 1852</date>
                        <salute>My dear Sir,</salute>
                    </opener>
                    <div type="transcription">
                        <p>I hope to be all day at Kew on the 22nd– if you could bring your party
                            then I might be of some little service to you – for would you like me to
                            give you a letter to Dr W. Hooker who might not be able to attend to you
                            himself but could put you under the guidance of some intelligent person
                            in the garden so as to secure your seeing what was most worthy your
                            attention? My son in law Dr Hooker is so much engaged that I cannot ask
                            him to go round with you – but I am sure my daughter will be happy to
                            see you &amp; render any assistance – they are however going to
                            Switzerland in August–</p>
                        <p>Yours very truly</p>
                        <p>J. S. Henslow</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </body>
